🧚‍♀️ Up for Pre-Order NOW from @sideshow & @jscottcampbellart - Tinkerbell “Fall Variant Statue”
🔗Link in profile

Seasons change but the magic remains …

Sideshow and fan-favorite artist J. Scott Campbell present an autumnal addition to J. Scott Campbell’s Fairytale Fantasies Collection, the Tinkerbell Fall Variant Statue.

Working closely with Campbell, Sideshow has translated his iconic artwork into a stunning three-dimensional celebration of his reimagined classic fairytale characters like Alice in Wonderland, the Little Mermaid, Cinderella, and Tinkerbell. This variant gives the whimsical fairy a seasonal new style to fit the changing foliage.

Tinkerbell stands 12” tall, strutting atop an intricate Neverland compass base that points the way to adventure. Detailed twin crocodiles are carved into the bronze-colored instrument, which has a realistic clear face beneath Tink’s delicate feet.

Based on J. Scott Campbell’s signature style, Tinkerbell shimmers with an air of mischievous magic. The polyresin pixie has detailed, translucent wings and a 12” wingspan, and her orange leaf dress is intricately sculpted with natural textures befitting the Neverland native. Her portrait features auburn hair with a light stripe, and her eyes and makeup compliment the colorful update. Tink’s look is completed with matching orange accessories including her necklace, armband, leg cuff, and the vines at her thigh.

If you believe in fairies, then spread your wings and welcome the Tinkerbell Fall Variant Statue to your collection today!
